title: Son of Kong (1933)
description:
The Son of Kong (1933

  70 min   -  Action | Adventure | Comedy

The men who captured the giant ape King Kong, return to his island and find his equally gigantic, but far more friendly, son. 

The Son of Kong is a 1933 American adventure film/monster movie produced by RKO Pictures. Directed by Ernest Schoedsack and featuring 
special effects by Buzz Gibson and Willis O'Brien, the film starred Robert Armstrong, Helen Mack and Frank Reicher. This film is the 
lesser known sequel to King Kong, and was released just nine months after its predecessor.
